-- Spain's Bankia sells Iberdrola stake at 4.85 euros/shr 
-- By Tracy Rucinski
-- Thu Apr 10, 2014 04:10AM EDT
-- None



MADRID, April 10 (Reuters) - Spain's biggest state-owned lender Bankia <BKIA.MC> has sold a 4.94 percent stake in Spanish utility Iberdrola <IBE.MC> at 4.85 euros per share, or a total of 1.53 billion euros ($2.1 billion), the book runners said in a statement on Thursday.

Bankia said capital gains from the sale were 266 million euros.